. He asked me what Ithought of the new book he was telling Morozov (a monolinguist)about--namely Maurois' "impressive work on Byron," and upon my answeringthat I had found it to be impressive trash, my austere critic muttered, "Idon't think you have read it," and went on educating the serene old poet.

I would steal away long before the party broke up. The sounds offarewells usually reached me as I glided into insomnia.

